HkvnR8R6z.content:
See utils-example-queue for example.

* all nodes of a single queue should have PUSH tied to same output. Same for POP.
* MEM of 1st node tied to NEW of 2nd node, repeat for entire queue.
* oMEM of last node tied to OLD of previous node, repeat for entire queue
* In order for queue-buffers to determine data type, the links from MEM/oMEM to NEW/OLD may need to route through explicit defer(data_type) nodes
*
* Works well for implementing stack
* Only partial solution for FIFO queue -- the 1st (queue_depth-1) outputs will be 0 as queue fills up

I would love to implement a variadic wrapper, but I can't figure out how to feed old values back up through the cascade for POP.
